.TH "nilfs_cpfile_get_stat" 9 "nilfs_cpfile_get_stat" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
nilfs_cpfile_get_stat \- get checkpoint statistics
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" nilfs_cpfile_get_stat
.BI "(struct inode *cpfile "  ","
.BI "struct nilfs_cpstat *cpstat "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "cpfile" 12
inode of checkpoint file
.IP "cpstat" 12
pointer to a structure of checkpoint statistics
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
\fBnilfs_cpfile_get_stat\fP returns information about checkpoints.

Return Value: On success, 0 is returned, and checkpoints information is
stored in the place pointed by \fIcpstat\fP. On error, one of the following
negative error codes is returned.

-EIO - I/O error.

-ENOMEM - Insufficient amount of memory available.
